&lt;div class="glossary-term" data-tag="federal">
&lt;h2 id="ami-area-median-income">AMI (Area Median Income)&lt;a class="anchor" href="#ami-area-median-income">#&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The median household income for a metropolitan area, calculated annually by HUD. Seattle&amp;rsquo;s AMI is used as the benchmark for defining affordable housing eligibility &amp;ndash; typically at percentages like 30%, 50%, 60%, or 80% of AMI.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>